bishop /ˈbɪʃəp/

(bishops) 

1. N-COUNT/N-TITLE/N-VOC A bishop is a clergyman of high rank in the Roman Catholic, Anglican, and Orthodox churches. (天主教、英国圣公会、东正教的) 主教 

2. N-COUNT In chess a bishop is a piece that can be moved diagonally across the board on squares that are the same colour. (国际象棋中的) 象

